<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ezra on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/</link><description>Recent content in Ezra on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Ezra 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-1">Ezra Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="cyrus-lets-the-exiles-return">Cyrus Lets the Exiles Return&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the first year of Cyrus, king of Persia, to fulfill his message through Jeremiah, Yahveh stirred up Cyrus. He sent a written proclamation everywhere in his kingdom:&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         2&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Cyrus, king of Persia, says, ‘Yahveh God of heaven has given me the kingdoms of the world and appointed me to build him a temple in Jerusalem, in Judah. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/b>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Whoever is from his people, your God be with you! Go up&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> and rebuild the Temple of Yahveh God of Israel, the God in Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>4&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Wherever there’s a survivor, support him with silver and gold, supplies and livestock, plus freewill offerings.’”           &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                                                                  &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-2">Ezra Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The People in the Province Who Went Up&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>from the Exiles Nebuchadnezzar Took Away&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'> They went to Jerusalem and their towns in Judah &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum, and Baanah: from the&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                                                                    3&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>famly of Parosh            2,172   &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>family of Shephatiah                   372&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-3">Ezra Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-altar-is-rebuilt">The Altar Is Rebuilt&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When the &lt;b>seventh month&lt;/b> came and the Israelites were in the towns, they came together in Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Jeshua Ben-Jozadak, his brothers the priests, Zerubbabel Ben-Shealtiel, and his brothers built God’s altar for offering burnt offerings as written in the Law of Moses, the man of God. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They set up the altar on its original site despite their fear of the people around them. They offered burnt offerings to Yahveh morning and evening. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They celebrated the Festival of Booths as written and offered the set number of burnt offerings daily as required by the Law. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>From then on, there was continual burnt offering for new moons and the annual festivals Yahveh had consecrated. Everyone offered a freewill offering to Yahveh. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>From the &lt;b>first day, seventh month&lt;/b>, they offered burnt offerings, but the foundation of the Temple hadn’t been laid. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then they donated money to the masons and carpenters as well as food, drink, and olive oil to the Sidonians and Tyrians to bring cedar from Lebanon by sea to Joppa with permission from Cyrus.&lt;b>
&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-4">Ezra Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When the enemies of Judah and Benjamin heard that the exiles were rebuilding a temple to Yahveh God of Israel, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>they approached Zerubbabel and the other leaders, &lt;i>“Let us build with you. We worship your God too. We’ve been sacrificing to him since Esarhaddon, king of Assyria, sent us here.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But Zerubbabel, Jeshua, and the other leaders said, &lt;i>“You don’t have anything in common with us building a temple to our God. We’ll build it like King Cyrus decreed.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-5">Ezra Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="tattenais-letter-to-darius">Tattenai’s Letter to Darius&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The prophets Haggai and Zechariah Ben-Iddo served as prophets to the Jews in Judah and Jerusalem in the name of the God of Israel. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then Zerubbabel and Jeshua started again to rebuild God’s Temple. His prophets supported them. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>At that time, Tattenai, governor of the province Beyond the River, and Shethar-bozenai, and their colleagues came and asked, &lt;i>“Who issued a decree for you to rebuild this Temple and restore this structure?” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>We told them the names of the men that were reconstructing it. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But God kept an eye on the elders of the Jews. They didn’t stop them till a report could go to Darius and a written reply could come back. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-6">Ezra Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="darius-decree">Darius’ Decree&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>King Darius issued an order to search the Babylonian archives, which were housed in the treasury. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But in the fortress in Ecbatana, in the province of Media, they found a scroll with the following written in it:&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            “Record:&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the &lt;b>first year of King Cyrus&lt;/b>, he issued a decree:&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>‘As to&lt;i> God’s Temple in Jerusalem, rebuild it, where sacrifices are offered. Keep its foundations the same. Its height and width are 90ft &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>with three courses of large stones alternating with one course of timbers. Pay for it out of the royal treasury. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Take back to God’s temple the gold and silver articles Nebuchadnezzar took from it.’
         &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-7">Ezra Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ezra-arrives-in-jerusalem">Ezra Arrives in Jerusalem&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>After that, &lt;b>in the reign of Artaxerxes&lt;/b>, king of Persia, &lt;i>came&lt;/i> Ezra Ben-Seraiah (&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ben-Azariah Ben-Hilkiah &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ben-Shallum Ben-Zadok Ben-Ahitub &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ben-Amariah Ben-Azariah Ben-Meraioth &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ben-Zerahiah Ben-Uzzi Ben-Bukki &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ben-Abishua Ben-Phinehas Ben-Eleazar)&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'> Ben-Aaron the chief priest. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Ezra, a scribe, an expert in the Law of Moses, came up from Babylon. The king granted him everything he requested because Yahveh’s hand was on him. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Some Israelites, priests, Levites, singers, gatekeepers, and Temple servants came up to Jerusalem in &lt;b>the seventh year of King Artaxerxes&lt;/b>. [&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>]
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v9" id="v9">&lt;sup class="verse-num">9&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>On the &lt;b>first day, first month&lt;/b>, &lt;i>Ezra&lt;/i> started out from Babylon. On the
&lt;b>first day, fifth month&lt;/b> he arrived at Jerusalem because God’s good hand was on him. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v10" id="v10">&lt;sup class="verse-num">10&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He had set his heart on studying the Law of Yahveh, practicing it, and teaching its statutes and ordinances in Israel.&lt;b>                            &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-8">Ezra Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Heads of Families and the Genealogies of Men&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-bottom:0in; text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>Who Went Up from Babylon During the Reign of King Artaxerxes&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>from the family of Phinehas, Gershom;        &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>from the family of Ithamar, Daniel;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>from the family of David, Hattush, &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  3&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a descendant of Shecaniah; &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 9</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-09/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-09/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-9">Ezra Chapter 9&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ezras-prayer-about-intermarriage">Ezra’s Prayer About Intermarriage&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When these things had been completed, the officials approached me, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“The people of Israel, the priests, and the Levites haven’t separated from the foreigners and the disgusting things of the Canaanites, Hittites, Perizzites, Jebusites, Ammonites, Moabites, Egyptians, and Amorites. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They’ve taken some of their daughters as wives for themselves and their sons. The holy race has intermingled with foreigners. The officials and rulers have been the most prominent in this unfaithfulness.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ezra 10</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-10/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/ezra/chapter-10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="ezra-chapter-10">Ezra Chapter 10&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-people-confess-their-sins">The People Confess Their Sins&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>While Ezra was praying and confessing, crying and prostrating himself in front of God’s Temple, a big crowd of men, women, and children gathered around him, sobbing with him. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Shecaniah Ben-Jehiel, one of Elam’s sons, told him, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“We’ve been unfaithful to our God and married foreign women from the land. But there’s still hope for Israel. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Let’s make a covenant with God to put away the wives and their children as you’ve advised and do it according to the Law. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Get up! This is your responsibility. We’ll be with you. Have the courage to do it.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>